There are different Types of the Rate Limiting Algorithms :
---------------------------------------------------------------------------- >
1) Fixed Window (used here)
2) Sliding Window
3) Token Bucket ⭐ (best for production)
4) Leaky Bucket




Token Based Rate Limit:
--------------------------------- >
>> Token bucket allows requests as long as tokens are available, and tokens are refilled gradually over time.

Start: 5 tokens
User sends 5 requests → ✅✅✅✅✅ (bucket empty)
Next request → ❌ blocked
After 10 sec → +1 token → ✅ allowed




Difference between Windows Based and Token based Rate Lmits:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ >
##  Express-rate-limit uses a fixed window algorithm, where a user can make a fixed number of requests within a time window, after which they are blocked until the window resets.

##  Token bucket, on the other hand, allows requests based on available tokens that refill over time. It supports burst traffic while maintaining a steady rate, making it more flexible and production-friendly.

Express-rate-limit uses a fixed window approach where a user can make a limited number of requests in a fixed time, and after that they are blocked completely until the window resets.

Token bucket works differently — it gives tokens that are consumed per request and refilled over time. This allows burst requests but still controls the overall rate, making it smoother and more flexible.










